TraceyMurryOZ
Glenmore Park, Australia144 contributions
5.0 of 5 bubbles
Paradise cruise 3 day/2 night cruise
Apr 2011
Having stayed at budget accommodation for most of our trip we decided to splurge on our cruise. I reviewed a variety of cruises through Tripadvisor and decided on a Paradise cruise. I booked the cruise through our hotel via email from Australia and they got us a much better price than through the Paradise's own website. And we didn’t have to pay anything until we settled our hotel bill at the end of our stay.
We were collected promptly from our hotel for the 4 hour trip to Halong Bay (toilet/shopping stop included) Arrived at the Cafe/wharf , given a lanyard designating which boat we were on (they have 3 almost identical boats) and then boarded a short time later. Up to the Dining room, keys allocated and off to our cabins. Our cabin was on the bottom deck and didn’t have a balcony (room was bigger) quick look around then up to the Dining room for a buffet lunch.
After lunch a look from the top deck then settled into some comfy lounge chairs with a view where we met some other Aussies and had a few drinks. Stopped at a fishing village where we were all rowed around by the local women (great photos) then on to a pearl farm for a look see ( and chance to buy) then back for a chance to make some spring rolls on the top deck (and sample them of course)
Another drink then a 5 course dinner in the beautiful dining room. More drinks (happy hour 9pm to 11pm drinks half price) and then bed
Day 2 all the 1 night people went to the caves while the 2 night people transferred to another smaller boat and were joined by the other 2 night people from the other Paradise cruise boats.
We were all taken to Cat Ba National Park? And asked on the way if we preferred to ride a pushbike or on the back of a scooter to the local village. The transport we requested was waiting for us when we arrived and we took a leisurely ride to the village for a look around and then a trek through the bush, a cave then back to the village and boat. A 5 course Vietnamese lunch while cruising among the limestone islands then a stop for a kayak or swim and back to our original boat by 3pm. Same activities repeated while we rested, another 5 course dinner to follow.
Day 3 we visited a cave with hundreds of other people (great photo op at the top ) then packed our bags and enjoyed the cruise back to the wharf. Worth every penny!!!
Written May 4, 2011
This review is the subjective opinion of a Tripadvisor member and not of Tripadvisor LLC. Tripadvisor performs checks on reviews as part of our industry-leading trust & safety standards. Read our transparency report to learn more.
